<td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_05.gif" class="headerbg"><font class="h1font"><font color="#FFFFFF"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Articles</td><form method='post' action=''><input type="hidden" name="PHPSESSID" value="...328fedb22570524062aeb1303" /><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Articles</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/starwarsccg/articles/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/vs/articles/index.php3'>Marvel VS</option><option value='/heroclix/articles/articles.php'>HeroClix</option><option value='/lotr/articles/articles.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/articles/articles.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/articles/articles.php'>Ophidian 2350</option><option value='/magic/treports/treports.php'>The Wastelands</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></B></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_06.gif"></td></tr>
	<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_07.gif"></td>
		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> The Power Behind the Mines of Moria<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.63)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=6439'>clarrie " DLOTSuckers" brown</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=6439&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> January 18, 2002</font><p align='justify'><font class="bfont"> This is an article that looks at the strengths and weaknesses of the super power that is the cave troll of Moria.First I will list some of the stats of the cave troll and then ill talk about his uses, weaknesses and strengths. <br />
<br />
Cave Troll:<br />
-Twilight cost 10<br />
-Strength 15<br />
-Vitality 4<br />
Fierce, damage +1<br />
&#8211;3 twilight cost at underground sites.<br />
<br />
At first glance this card looks as if it is a very good card but some people may be turned off it by its high deploy cost And its moria orc logo. Although the Cave troll does have a expensive cost it can easily be brought down by of course  its its own text and the other way is the trolls keyward which if on table brings the cave troll down another 2 in cost so if he is at an underground site and the keyward is on table he comes down for a net cost of  7 which is very reasonable for what catastrophe and damage he causes. Another way that the cave trolls cost can indirectly be brought down is through the goblin runners. The goblin runners are a deceptive way of bringing the cave trolls cost down as they come down and add 2 to the pool which usually becomes net cost of adding 1 to the pool. So especially for beginners if  they have a cave troll, but no keyward to bring down the cost, and they find that they never can get the troll down due to his high cost, a very effective way is to get a couple of runners down to get it down cheaper. Host of thousands also allows you to get the runners or the keyward to keep coming back.  <br />
<br />
 The main disadvantage of the cave troll is the fact that he is a troll and that most of the moria orc (which is the deck he almost every time goes in.) cards do not work on him and the only weapon that goes on him is of course the cave trolls hammer or if you are a beginner you can use the goblin spear as it deploys on a Moria minion unlike most Moria weapons that deploy on an orc. Some people say that the cave troll is a once a table minion and that after one use he will either not hit the table again or he simply wont be of any use anymore others base their deck around the cave troll continuously coming out with his big spanking stick and decimating your opponent site after site. There is many ways of bringing the cave troll or keyward pair back and making the deck that relies on the cave troll coming out often effective the most efficient way is through the nazgul minion that lets you bring a minion back from your discard pile which lets you get back the cave troll or the keyward which ever you do not have iin your hand. Another way that you can bring back the keyward is through host of thousands although this does not work with the cave troll it still lets you bring back the keyward so you don&#8217;t have to keep searching for the pair every time you want to put them down other ways to bring the keyward back is through They are Coming and Goblin Swarm,s although he has to win a skirmish first. <br />
<br />
I find the best use for the cave troll is to use only one or two and not to rely on him to come down near every turn with his stick making him 18 power and +2 damage to try and kill a companion all the time. Usually most players unless they are paying a sprint deck will not double move into site 5 and therefore will wait at site 4. So try to keep the troll saved in your hand until then so when they move into site 5 put him down cheaper and a couple of cheap orcs or even the keyward of course not FORGETTING that the DISADVANTAGE of the cave troll is that you have to spot a moria orc to play him in the first place. By putting the cave troll down at site 5 in 9.99/10 cases stops the fellowship moving on and if you are able to move past site 5 without being stopped then you will always be a site ahead and by setting this pace your opponent may panic run past the sanctuary and he&#8217;ll be easy pickings for your orc swarms.<br />
<br />
I hope you have gained something from this article and by using some information in this article use my favourite minion in the LotR TCG the Cave Troll of Moria. Thanks for reading and enjoy and keep improving Decktech.    <br />
<br />
